## R Markdown

``` r
counts <- read.csv("airway_scaledcounts.csv", stringsAsFactors = FALSE)
metadata <-  read.csv("airway_metadata.csv", stringsAsFactors = FALSE)
```

How many genes are we dealing with?

``` r
nrow(counts)
```

    ## [1] 38694

We want to calculate the average counts per gene for control samples and
for the drug treated samples. We will compare these values to see if
there is a difference in gene expression.

Now I want access to the control only column in the metadata

``` r
control <- metadata[metadata$dex == "control",]
control
```

# Set the color palette for our plot

``` r

mycols[ res$log2FoldChange < -2 ] <- "blue"
plot(res$log2FoldChange, -log(res$padj), col=mycols)
abline(v=c(-2,2), col="darkgray", lty=2)
```
